WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
narrator: drive real traffic across the three-peer mesh.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:15.000
narrator: the bringup script is idempotent — fast when already up.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:50.000
narrator: docker compose pulls cached images; build is warm.

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:40.000
narrator: the mesh converges to READY before the traffic burst.

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:14.000
narrator: discover peer-2 and peer-3 IPs from peer-1 status output.

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:24.000
narrator: control-plane ping rides the encrypted tailscale plane.

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:38.000
narrator: a second ping to peer-3 confirms full-mesh reachability.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:55.000
narrator: a tiny busybox HTTP target boots inside peer-2.

00:02:55.000 --> 00:03:04.000
narrator: peer-1 fetches bytes from peer-2 — the data plane is live.

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:13.000
narrator: the policy CRUD endpoint is the placeholder for post-Hub.

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:28.000
narrator: teardown — a clean handoff to the metrics tape.
